    <div class="article-content">
        <div class="sub-content-header">Shapiro Brings CES News, Innovation Outlook to SXSW</div>
        <span class="smallText">Mar 12, 2012 11:50:46</span>
        
        
        <p>On Monday, March 12, Consumer Electronics Association (CEA) CEO Gary Shapiro will be attending a variety of events at the <a  href="http://sxsw.com/interactive">South by Southwest Interactive</a> festival. With thousands in attendance focusing on entrepreneurs delivering the newest technologies and services, Shapiro will be revealing how entrepreneurs will play a vital role at the 2013 International CES.<br />
        <br />
        And Shapiro, The New York Times bestselling author of <a  href="http://www.amazon.com/Comeback-Innovation-Restore-American-Dream/dp/0825305624">The Comeback: How Innovation Will Restore the American Dream</a>, will share his unique insights on the role of innovation in our nation’s economic renewal.<br />
        <br />
        Please stop by to talk to or see Gary at one of the following stops:</p>
        <p><strong>Startup America Live<br />
        </strong>Gary will be joining our friends at the Startup America Partnership at 9:30 a.m. at the Startup Village (Austin Downtown Hilton, 500 East 4th Street). Gary will appear on Valleygirl.tv with other luminaries during his time at the village. Gary will be revealing our exciting news to Valleygirl.tv host Jesse Draper, among other topics.</p>
        <p><strong>South by Southwest Bookstore<br />
        </strong>At 3 p.m. Gary will be signing books at the SXSW Bookstore. Come get your blueprint to an innovation-based economy and get Gary’s signature. (Austin Convention Center, Level 4, Ballroom D Foyer)</p>
        <p><strong>The Future of Innovation and Consumer Electronics<br />
        </strong>From 5 to 6 p.m. (Austin Convention Center, Ballroom EF), Gary will join TechTalk’s Kevin O’Malley and Essential’s Richard Watson to discuss how consumer electronics are driving innovation in the U.S. and abroad. With our most successful CES ever just a few months behind us, expect Gary to share his unique view on the role of consumer electronics in technology. Put it on your calendar!</p>
        <p>Read more: <a href="http://blog.ce.org/index.php/2012/03/08/shapiro-brings-ces-news-innovation-outlook-to-sxsw/#ixzz1ouzu1wd1">http://blog.ce.org/index.php/2012/03/08/shapiro-brings-ces-news-innovation-outlook-to-sxsw/#ixzz1ouzu1wd1</a></p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
    
    
