    <img src="/images/photos/2012-CE-Week.jpg">
    <div class="article-content">
        <div class="sub-content-header">2012 CE Week Showcases Global Brands and Innovators In NYC</div>
        <span class="smallText">Feb 28, 2012 12:38:06</span>
        
        
        <p>CE Week, the consumer electronics and technology industry's annual mid-year event returns to New York City on June 25-29, 2012. CE Week brings together global companies and innovators for conferences, exhibitions, workshops and networking events, including the ever-popular CEA Line Shows and Digital Downtown Conference scheduled for June 27-28, 2012 at the Altman Building and Metropolitan Pavilion. <a  href="http://www.ceweekny.com">CE Week</a> is a unique event as it allows companies to customize their participation and be promoted within this week of activities focusing on consumer technology.</p>
        <p>New for the <a  href="http://www.ceweekny.com">2012 CE Week</a>:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Eureka Park Challenge: Building off the success of the Eureka Park TechZone at the 2012 International CES, this competition will showcase innovative new technology products and services from the hottest companies and startups. After online judging, 10 finalists will be selected to participate in the "Eureka Park Challenge" at the CEA Line Shows. These companies will be featured within a two-day interactive exhibit area and competition, with live on-stage presentations to determine the top company. Winners of the Eureka Park Challenge will receive free booth space at the 2013 International CES.</li>
            <li>Mobile Apps Showdown: Produced by Robin Raskin and Living in Digital Times, the Mobile Apps Showdown NYC Competition will determine the best app across the top smartphone platforms. Apps producers will have two minutes to demo their app, and an applause-o-meter will measure audience enthusiasm to determine the winners.</li>
            <li>6Sight Conference: A series of executive conferences that will focus on the impact the imaging industry and its technologies have on society, and the revenue possibilities they enable. The participants will preview breakthrough technologies, forecast innovative uses, and spark new ideas and alliances that benefit current and potential customers, participating companies, and the imaging industry as a whole.</li>
            <li>mHealth NYC: Tech leaders will talk about mobile tech devices, networks and services.</li>
            <li>2nd Screen Summit: A program focusing on the multi-screen TV experience and the social TV revolution.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>"CE Week and the CEA Line Shows continue to grow in importance and relevance as the mid-year business event for our industry," said Gary Shapiro, CEA president and CEO. "The 2012 CE Week looks to be the best event yet, with more partners, more participants and more events than ever. I encourage the tech industry to register and make plans now to be at this must-attend event this June."</p>
        <p>The 2011 CE Week drew more than 5,500 attendees, including more than 640 media/analysts and 430 retailer/distributors, making it one of the CE industry's biggest annual events. More than 200 companies and 17 event partners converged to showcase the best new products for back-to-school and the holidays. The official CE Week TV channel, GeekBeat TV, reached one million viewers with its event coverage.</p>
        <p>Registration for the <a  href="http://www.ceweekny.com">2012 CE Week is open now</a>. For more information about CE Week and the CEA Line Shows visit <a  href="http://www.ceweekny.com">www.ceweekny.com</a> and <a href="http://www.cealineshows.com">www.cealineshows.com</a>. </p>
    
    
